#: ../../library/array.rst:55
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"``array('u')`` now uses :c:type:`wchar_t` as C type instead of deprecated "
"``Py_UNICODE``. This change doesn't affect its behavior because "
"``Py_UNICODE`` is alias of :c:type:`wchar_t` since Python 3.3."
